<br>
I wonder what i should do now that my schoolwork is all done...?<br>
<br>
Seriously, i will finish up all the loose ends and have them done soon. I hope that cheers everyone up.<br>
<br>
I thought about putting up the photoshop templates, but they are rather big in that format, they are tough to upload because i only get 8 megabytes on my service, and then people would make their own and we would have all kinds of quality control issues. I have fairly good knowledge of collectable card games and I try to get everything ballenced out right, plus i have all the cards i've worked on in the past for backup ideas, and i've got the jist of it in my head.<br>
<br>
I am actually saving you work, all you have to do is email me with your ideas. If you leave it up to me to root around the Works In Prograss forum to find your stuff, thats an inconvinience for me, you get it?<br>
<br>
New policy: Feel free to invent any ideas for cards, the more specific the better. if you draw something for a card or invet one, I will attribute it to you by using your illustration and your name will appeear on it in the Illustrator line. However, since i am using the idea that your cards all or mostly work by a unifying stratagy (such as Mylak's cards mostly being furry, or Demosthene's cards mostly dealling with triggered effects from action cards being played) I am allowing this: talk to me, and you can re-illustrate a card that someone else thought of if it goes with your stratagy, and it becomes your card. That, or there will be two versions with slightly different effects. That way people who notice cards allready in existance and think of ideas for a deck stratagy will be able to get the cards they want for their decks.<br>
<br>
Also, these cards are not set in stone. if you have any problems or suggestions for any card that has already been made, just tell me, and i can easily change it. This allows for better balence when more cards have been made, or if an artist gets better and thinks thay deserve more points for their card.<br>
<br>
Keep the ideas coming, and remember, Email them to me! heh heh, see ya! <p><BR>
